// =============================================================================
// core-tests/net/udp/unit_test.vr — data-surface coverage
// =============================================================================
//
// `core/net/udp.vr` (~1060 LOC) — UDP datagram sockets via V-LLSI
// syscalls. Used for DNS (RFC 1035 §4.2.1), QUIC, multicast.
//
// Live operations require socket bind + send_to/recv_from which is
// gated on `vcs/specs/L2-standard/net/udp/` harness.
//
// Data-surface from `udp.vr`: `UdpSocket` record is the only public
// type (record fields are internal: fd, local_addr, peer_addr).
//
// This file is intentionally minimal until a UDP-loopback harness
// lands. UdpSocket bind/connect/send_to/recv_from coverage is at
// L2 specs.
// =============================================================================

mount core.net.udp.{UdpSocket};

// =============================================================================
// Section 1: UdpSocket — import-only smoke test
// =============================================================================
//
// The `UdpSocket` constructor and method surface require runtime
// socket binding — see audit.md §3.1. This smoke test confirms the
// type symbol resolves through the import path.

@test
fn test_udp_socket_type_imports() {
    // Type resolves through `mount core.net.udp.{UdpSocket}` —
    // confirms module imports + sysmlib precompile cascade reach
    // this submodule without precompile-cascade SIGSEGV.
    assert(true);
}
